  <summary>6/11/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968 to provide a lump sum payment of $50,000 to public safety officers (law enforcement officers and fire fighters) who become permanently and totally disabled as a result of a catastrophic injury sustained in the line of duty. Prohibits the payment of both a lump sum disability payment and a lump sum death benefit.</summary>
